  "prompt": "What career advice would you give to someone who wants to become a nuerosurgeon?",
  "response": "Here's some career advice for aspiring neurosurgeons:\n\n1. Academic Preparation\n- Excel in science and math courses during high school\n- Pursue a strong undergraduate degree in pre-med or sciences\n- Maintain a high GPA (3.5+)\n- Score well on the MCAT\n\n2. Medical School\n- Get accepted to a reputable medical school\n- Focus on neuroscience, anatomy, and related coursework\n- Participate in research opportunities\n- Maintain top academic performance\n\n3. Residency\n- Complete a competitive neurosurgery residency program\n- Typically 7 years long and highly demanding\n- Develop advanced surgical skills\n- Build professional network\n\n4. Personal Qualities\n- Develop exceptional hand-eye coordination\n- Build strong stress management skills\n- Cultivate patience and precision\n- Demonstrate excellent communication skills\n- Maintain physical and mental stamina\n\n5. Additional Recommendations\n- Consider fellowship in a subspecialty\n- Stay updated on technological advances\n- Join professional organizations\n- Be prepared for long hours and significant commitment\n- Develop strong interpersonal skills for patient care\n\n6. Financial Preparation\n- Understand significant educational expenses\n- Plan for potential student loan management\n- Recognize high earning potential after training\n\nThis path requires dedication, intelligence, and substantial personal investment.",
